node.text:
A thousand photos will still not prepare you for Bryce Canyon in person. 
•••••
Thanks to @get.out_there for the Bryce Canyon experience. 
•
📍Bryce Canyon National Park, UT

🇬🇧 Our first hike in Bryce Canyon was the famous Navajo Loop trail that we combined with the Queen’s Garden trail. We decided to go down the canyon by the Wall Street switchbacks (pictured here) and highly recommend to do the hike that way. It would be sad to miss the beautiful view! 

🇫🇷 Pour notre première randonnée à Bryce Canyon, nous avons combiné le sentier Navajo Loop avec le Queen’s Garden, et nous avons descendu dans le canyon par Wall Street. Nous recommandons à 100% de faire la balade dans cet ordre! Ça serait quand même dommage de manquer ces superbes points de vue!

node.text:
You never know who will say hello on an adventure to Channel Islands NP. 
•••••
Thanks to Eric @esmith_images for sharing the awesome experience. 
•
When I signed up for the annual @americancetaceansociety LA chapter’s all day excursion to explore the Santa Barbara Channel yesterday, I never expected to see Killer Whales! What an incredible interaction with three members of the CA39A pod. We also saw a few Humpback cow/calf pairs, a Minke whale, thousands of common dolphins, a Sea Lion colony on San Miguel Island, brown boobies and more. The waters around California’s Channel Islands National Park are some of the most stunning in the state. It was great to connect with old friends and the local whale die hards. Swipe through the gallery for a few of my favorite shots so far.
